observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.	Ensure that the Municipal Accountant and the GSO-Designate reconcile their respective records to ascertain the accuracy of the PPE balances in the financial statements;

b.	Initiate the disposal of unserviceable PPEs for dropping from the books of the agency using the IIRUP;

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.	Through the Local Development Planning Office, establish the GAD database with adequate and systematically gathered sex-disaggregated data which will provide the bases for gender analysis, planning, programming and policy formulation; 

b.	Establish a GAD Monitoring and Evaluation system that will evaluate if applied gender interventions responded to the gender issues identified; and

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Create/reconstitute an Inventory Committee for the conduct of a complete and detailed physical count of all the Municipality's properties;
Require the Municipal Accountant and the GSO-Designate to reconcile their respective records to ascertain the accuracy of the PPE balances in the financial statements;
Initiate the disposal of unserviceable PPEs for dropping from the books of the agency using the IIRUP;
Derecognize from the books the PPE accounts costing below P15,000.00 totaling ₱6,253,629.13; and
Comply with COACircularNo.2020-006 on the one-time cleansing of PPE.

Management comment:
The Municipal Accountant and Budget Officer acknowledged the lapses and will propose for the creation of a General Services Officer who will be in­ charge in the property and supply management of the municipality.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a. require the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to issue official receipts or acknowledgement receipt of the donations whether cash or in-kind;



b. 	take heed of the basic controls in the receipt, recording, inventory, storage and distribution of all donations received during calamities;


c. require the Committee in-charge of the Physical Inventory to include In-kind Donations received by the Municipality in the physical count and Inventory Report; 

d. submit the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances of cash and in-kind donations for CY 2020; and 

e. the Municipality to comply with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2014-002 on the accounting and reporting of cash and in-kind donations.

We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
require the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to issue receipt official receipts and acknowledgement of the donations whether cash or in-kind;
take heed of the basic controls in the receipt, recording, inventory, storage and distribution of all donations received during calamities;
require the Committee in-charge of the Physical Inventory to include In-kind Donations received by the Municipality in the physical count and Inventory Report;
(d) submit the Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances of cash and in-kind donations for CY 2020; and
(e) the Municipality to comply with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2014-002 on the accounting and reporting of cash and in-kind donations.

We recommended and management agreed to:
 notify the contractor on the deficiencies noted on the variation order amounting to ₱165,928.70;
 initiate the refund of the same through the withholding of payments to the contractor, if any.

We recommended that management:
 require the GAD Focal Point to administer the HGDG test on the LGU’s GAD PPAs in the preparation of Accomplishment Report, as basis for determining the actual expenditure that can be attributed to the GAD Budget;
 administer the HGDG test on its PPAs for CY 2017, the results of which shall be the basis in estimating the cost of gender mainstreaming and GAD Budget.
